<p>I prefer defining function as variable:</p>

<pre><code>let first = function(x){
   return x[0];
}
</code></pre>

<p>Instead of:</p>

<pre><code>function first(){
    ....
}
</code></pre>

<p>Because i can use expressions and decorators when defining the function. For example:</p>

<pre><code>let safe = function(f){
  try {f()...}
}
let last = safe(function(x){return x[0]}).
</code></pre>

<p>Also with ES6 its much shorter:</p>

<pre><code> let last = x =&gt; x[0]
 ...........
 function last(x){
     return x[0];
 }
......

let last = safe(x =&gt; x[0]);
</code></pre>
